FILE HANDLING:
==============
- File is used to store large data, permanent storage
- File is a collection of records and records are collection of fields
- Syntax 
DCL filename FILE attributes
- filename: It's a logical file name to be used in program and same filename will be used as DD name in JCL
- Types of Attributes:
 - Alternative Attributes
- STREAM/RECORD
 - STREAM attribute process continuous stream of data items in character format
   - STREAM file operation can be done using OPEN, CLOSE, GET, PUT
 - RECORD attribute process the collection of records.
 - RECORD file operation can be done using OPEN,CLOSE,READ,WRITE,REWRITE,DELETE
 - If both STREAM and RECORD are omitted then STREAM is default attribute

- INPUT/OUTPUT/UPDATE
 - INPUT is used to transmit the data from the dataset to program variable
 - INPUT is used for operation READ
 - OUTPUT is used to transmit the data from program variables to dataset
 - OUTPUT is used for operation WRITE
 - UPDATE is used for transmitting the data in either directions
 - UPDATE is used for operation REWRITE,DELETE
 - If opening option is not coded the INPUT is the default attribute

- SEQUENTIAL/DIRECT
 - SEQUENTIAL is used to access the records in consecutive order
 - DIRECT is used to access the records directly based on the key value


 - Additive Attributes
- KEYED
 - It applies only to the records files which is associated with INDEXED and RELATIVE datasets
- ENV(VSAM)
 - It denotes VSAM datasets

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

- Sequential Update in PS Dataset:
DEMO09:PROC OPTIONS(MAIN);

 /*********************************************************************/
 /*  DECLARING THE ATTRIBUTES OF THE DATASET                          */
 /*********************************************************************/
    DCL INFILE FILE RECORD UPDATE SEQUENTIAL;

 /*********************************************************************/
 /* VARIABLE TO HOLD A RECORD                                         */
 /*********************************************************************/
    DCL 1 CUST_RECORD,
        2 CT_CUSTOMERID       PIC '(04)9',
        2 CT_CUSTOMERNAME     PIC '(20)A',
        2 CT_CUSTOMERMAIL     PIC '(30)X',
        2 CT_CUSTOMERMOB      PIC '(10)9';
 /*********************************************************************/
 /* VARIABLES TO HANDLE ERRORS                                        */
 /*********************************************************************/
    DCL EOF BIN(1) INIT('0'B);
    DCL CUSTID   PIC   '(4)9';
    DCL CUSTMAIL PIC   '(30)X';

 /*********************************************************************/
 /* HANDLING THE ERROR CONDITION IF FILE OPEN FAILS                   */
 /*********************************************************************/
    ON ENDFILE(INFILE)
    BEGIN;
EOF = '1'B;
    END;


 /*********************************************************************/
 /* ACCEPT THE CUSTOMER ID  FROM THE USER                             */
 /*********************************************************************/
    GET LIST(CUSTID);
    GET SKIP LIST(CUSTMAIL);

    OPEN FILE(INFILE) UPDATE;

    READ FILE(INFILE) INTO(CUST_RECORD);

    DO UNTIL(EOF ='1'B)
      IF CT_CUSTOMERID = CUSTID THEN
        DO;
        CT_CUSTOMERMAIL=CUSTMAIL;
        REWRITE FILE(INFILE) FROM(CUST_RECORD);
        END;
        READ FILE(INFILE) INTO(CUST_RECORD);
    END;

    CLOSE FILE(INFILE);

 END DEMO09;

