EXCEPTION HANDLING:
===================
- Condition is an occurrence within a PL1 program that caused a program interrupt
- ON statement defines the action to take when the specified condition is signaled
- I/O conditions like  {ENDFILE, KEY, RECORD, UNDEFINEDFILE} are always enabled and may not be disabled
- Condition like {CONVERSIOM, FIXEDOVERFLOW, OVERFLOW, UNDERFLOW, ZERODIVIDE} are enabled always unless explicitly disabled.
- Condition SIZE is disabled unless it is explicitly enabled
- Changing the status of conditions through a CONDITION PREFIX
- EX: (NOFIXEDOVERFLOW): SUM=A+B+C;
- The word NO.. is used to tell that the condition is disabled

- Types of Conditions:
  - ENDFILE
- It is used during get read operations on file, this condition is enabled by default

  - UNDEFINEDFILE
- It is raised on successful attempt to open a file and this condition is also enabled by default

  - RECORD
- It is raised on an unsuccessful attempt to read a file or write into a file because of record size mismatch, it is enabled by default

  - OVERFLOW
- It is raised for floating point variables, it occurs when magnitude of floating point number exceeds the max value and this condition is enabled by default
- Max value for decimal and floating point numbers are 10^75 and 2^252

  - ZERODIVIDE
- It occurs when a number is made to divide a decimal value by 0, it is enable by default

  - STRINGSIZE
- It occurs during assignment operation when the destination string is shorter than the source string, it is disabled by default

  - SUBSCRIPTRANGE
- It occurs whenever an element outside the boundaries of an array is referenced, it is disabled by default

- Built-in functions:
  - Used in an on-unit for CONVERSION condition or in an ERROR on-unit
  - ONCODE
- Returns the type of interrupt that caused the on-unit to become active
- Returns 0 if used in some statement other than ON statement

  - ONLOC
- Return the entry point of the procedure in which the interrupt was raised

  - ONCHAR
- Returns the character that caused the CONVERSION condition to be raised
- When used out of context it returns blank

  -ONSOURCE
- Returns the contents of the source field that caused CONVERSION condition to be raised
- When used out of context it returns null string

 (STRZ):
  STRING:
  PROC OPTIONS(MAIN);
  DCL SRC CHAR(20);
  DCL DEST CHAR(15);
  SRC='INFOSYS TECHNOLOGIES';
  ON STRINGSIZE
     PUT('INVALID STRNG ASSIGNMENT');
  PUT SKIP LIST(SRC);
  PUT SKIP LIST(DEST);
  DEST=SRC;
  PUT SKIP LIST(SRC);
  PUT SKIP LIST(DEST);
  END STRING;